        <h1 align="center">WHAT IS MENTAL HEALTH?</h1>
        <h2><u>MENTAL HEALTH</u></h2>
        <p>It is the complete physical, mental and social well being and not merely the absence of disease of infirmity.

        </p>
        <h2>A Few Facts </h2>
        <ul>
            <li>One in 5 people take time off work due to mental health </li>
            <li>92% of employees feel that mental health first aid and response is a very important issue</li>
            <li>While an alarming 48% of employees feel their workplace is a mentally unsafe place to work.</li>

        </ul> 
            <p>With this growing issue becoming a real challenge for employers, mental health support and recovery costs Australian’s $10.6B in 2018-19 which has been increasing by 1.5% each year since 2014. ref – headsup.org.au & aihw.gov.au</p>
        </p> 
        <p>It is definitely NOT easy being a teenager!
            Sometimes it's tough to avoid feeling stressed, and pressure can build up in many areas in life(socially, at home and while making big life decisions).</p>

        <p><i>   Worring about these pressures is NORMAL But feeling Very sad,hopeless or worthless might be a sign of a mental health problem.</i></p>
        <p> WARNING SIGNALS OF POOR MENTAL HEALTH</p>
        <ul>
            <li>are you always worrying? 
            </li>
            <li>Are you unable to concentrate because of unrecognised reasons?</li>
            <li>Are you continually unhappy without justified cause?</li>
            <li>Do you lose temper easily and often?</li>
            <li>Do you continually dislike to be with people?</li>
            <li>Do you have wide fluctuations in your mood?</li>
        
            <li>Are you troubled by regular insomnia?</li>
        
        </ul>
